<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON 16709 AND 16710 SERIES - REASSEMBLE - SYNCHRONIZER ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="5">
        <title>SYNCHRONIZER ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the larger LO range synchronizer ring on a bench. Install the sliding clutch, recessed
                side up, on blocker pins (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021b3">Figure 113</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021b3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021b3" filename="../figg13/G13021b3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 113. Install Sliding Clutch</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the three springs in the bores of the HI range synchronizer ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021b4">Figure 114</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021b4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021b4" filename="../figg13/G13021b4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 114. Install Springs</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the HI range synchronizer ring over the blocker pins of the LO range synchronizer,
                seating the springs against the pins (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021b5">Figure 115</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021b5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021b5" filename="../figg13/G13021b5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 115. Seat Springs Against Pins</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply downward pressure to the HI range synchronizer ring WHILE TWISTING COUNTERCLOCKWISE to
                compress the springs and fully seat the ring on the blocker pins of the LO range synchronizer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021b6">Figure 116</hotlnk>). It is suggested that a shop towel be placed over the
                synchronizer to prevent injury to your hands.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021b6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021b6" filename="../figg13/G13021b6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 116. Compress Springs</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the synchronizer assembly on the splines of the output shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021b7">Figure 117</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021b7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021b7" filename="../figg13/G13021b7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 117. Install Synchronizer Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
